{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17648625","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17648625"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T20:55:44+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T20:55:44+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18324"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18324","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18324"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.19,0.51,0.24,0.05,0.01]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11042"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"79800"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"11042","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/11042"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18324"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65108"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4931"},{"type":"tags","id":"4940"},{"type":"tags","id":"4946"},{"type":"tags","id":"7675"},{"type":"tags","id":"8403"},{"type":"tags","id":"9968"},{"type":"tags","id":"11272"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"25621"},{"type":"contributions","id":"25625"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"79800","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/79800"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following components of connective tissue primarily provides tensile strength and resistance to bending in bone?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Elastin","Collagen","Hydroxyapatite","Proteoglycans","Long chain hyaluronic acid"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EConnective tissue is composed of various components that contribute to its structural properties. In bone, certain components provide strength and resistance to mechanical forces.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECollagen\u003C/strong\u003E, specifically type I collagen, is the primary component of the organic matrix in bone. It provides tensile strength and resistance to bending. \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EProteoglycans\u003C/strong\u003E - These contribute to compressive strength by attracting water, but do not provide tensile strength.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHydroxyapatite\u003C/strong\u003E - Hydroxyapatite is the primary mineral component of bone and provides compressive strength, enabling bone to withstand weight and pressure.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ELong chain hyaluronic acid\u003C/strong\u003E - Hyaluronic acid is a glycosaminoglycan involved in providing viscosity and lubrication in synovial fluid and in the extracellular matrix of soft connective tissues. It has little structural role in bone, especially concerning tensile strength or bending resistance.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EElastin\u003C/strong\u003E - Elastin is a protein that provides elasticity and the ability to return to the original shape after stretching or deformation. It is abundant in tissues like skin, blood vessels, and ligaments but is not a major component of bone.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Collagen is a major component of connective tissue and provides tensile strength and resistance to bending.","Proteoglycans contribute to the compressive strength of connective tissues by attracting water.","Hydroxyapatite is a mineral that provides rigidity and hardness to bone.","Hyaluronic acid is a component of the extracellular matrix that provides lubrication and hydration."],"references":["Khurana, I., Khurana, A., \u0026 Kowlgi, N. G. (2019). Textbook of Medical Physiology_-E-book. Elsevier Health Sciences.","Datta HK, Ng WF, Walker JA, Tuck SP, Varanasi SS. The cell biology of bone metabolism. J Clin Pathol. 2008 May;61(5):577-87. doi: 10.1136/jcp.2007.048868. PMID: 18441154.","Patton, K. T., \u0026 Thibodeau, G. A. (2018). Anthony\u0027s Textbook of Anatomy \u0026 Physiology-E-Book: Anthony\u0027s Textbook of Anatomy \u0026 Physiology-E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences.","Smith, R., \u0026 Wordsworth, P. (2016). Oxford textbook of clinical and biochemical disorders of the skeleton. Oxford University Press."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65108"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18324"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65108","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/65108"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-15T21:36:05+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-15T21:37:33+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11042"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"79800"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":nul